    • Method Detail

      • readSingleBlock

        byte[] readSingleBlock(byte blockAddress)
                throws STException
        Read Single Block command as defined in NFC Forum Type 5 specification. Reads the content of one memory block (command code 0x20). Uses the default flag that was set in TagCommand.setFlag(). Uses the default uid that was set in TagCommand.setUid().
        Parameters:
        blockAddress - Address of the block to read
        Returns:
        array of bytes = 1 byte response flag + the content of the block (Little endian, or LSByte first)
        Throws:
        STException - STException

      • readSingleBlock

        byte[] readSingleBlock(byte blockAddress,
                       byte flag,
                       byte[] uid)
                throws STException
        Read Single Block command as defined in NFC Forum Type 5 specification. Reads the content of one memory block (command code 0x20).
        Parameters:
        blockAddress - Address of the block to read
        flag - Request flag for the command
        uid - Tag's UID (used only if the Select or Addressed mode bits are set in the flag)
        Returns:
        array of bytes = 1 byte response flag + the content of the block (Little endian, or LSByte first)
        Throws:
        STException - STException

      • writeSingleBlock

        byte writeSingleBlock(byte blockAddress,
                      byte[] buffer)
               throws STException
        Write Single Block command as defined in NFC Forum Type 5 specification. Updates the content of one memory block (command code 0x21). Uses the default flag that was set in TagCommand.setFlag(). Uses the default uid that was set in TagCommand.setUid().
        Parameters:
        blockAddress - Address of the block to write
        buffer - Data to write (Little endian, or LSByte first)
        Returns:
        1 byte response for status

      • writeMultipleBlock

        byte writeMultipleBlock(byte blockAddress,
                        byte nbrOfBlocks,
                        byte[] buffer)
                 throws STException
        Write Multiple Block command as defined in NFC Forum Type 5 specification. Write the content of one or more memory blocks (command code 0x24). Uses the default flag that was set in TagCommand.setFlag(). Uses the default uid that was set in TagCommand.setUid().
        Parameters:
        blockAddress - Address of the block to write
        nbrOfBlocks - The number of blocks in the request is one less than the number of blocks expected in the response.
        buffer - Data to write (Little endian, or LSByte first)
        Returns:
        1 byte response for status
        Throws:
        STException - STException

      • readMultipleBlock

        byte[] readMultipleBlock(byte blockAddress,
                         byte nbrOfBlocks)
                  throws STException
        Read Multiple Block command as defined in NFC Forum Type 5 specification. Read the content of one or more memory blocks (command code 0x23). Uses the default flag that was set in TagCommand.setFlag(). Uses the default uid that was set in TagCommand.setUid().
        Parameters:
        blockAddress - Address of the first block to read
        nbrOfBlocks - The number of blocks in the request is one less than the number of blocks that the VICC shall return in its response.
        Returns:
        array of bytes = 1 byte response flag + the content of the selected block (Little endian, or LSByte first)
        Throws:
        STException - STException

      • extendedReadMultipleBlock

        byte[] extendedReadMultipleBlock(byte[] blockAddress,
                                 byte[] numberOfBlocks)
                          throws STException
        Extended Read Multiple Block command as defined in NFC Forum Type 5 specification. Read the content of one or more blocks in an Extended memory (command code 0x33). Uses the default flag that was set in TagCommand.setFlag(). Uses the default uid that was set in TagCommand.setUid().
        Parameters:
        blockAddress - Address of the first block to read (2-byte address, LSByte first)

        Returns:
        array of bytes = 1 byte response flag + the content of the selected blocks (Little endian, or LSByte first)
        Throws:
        STException - STException
